Billionaire heiress and disc jockey DJ Cuppy has reacted to Kanye West’s claim to be the richest black man in the world. The US rapper, now known as Ye, recently featured on the talk show, “Hollywood Unlocked” where he ranted about being prevented by security operatives from seeing his kids despite being “the richest black man.” “My daughter wanted me to go inside. I was like, I am the richest black man and North’s father, right, and the security was able to stop me from going into the room with my daughter and that had not been defined,” he said in part.   Visually impaired fan gets N100,000 for mimicking Yul…     Portable: Olamide has become my benefactor     Samklef blames Nollywood for rise in ritual killings   Reacting via the microblogging app, Cuppy said although she’s an ardent fan of the 44-year-old “Donda” crooner, she disapproves of his claim about being the richest black man. - Advertisement - The “Gelatto” singer reminded the father of four that her godfather, Aliko Dangote is in fact the ‘richest black man.’ “Random, I know… I am a huge @KanyeWest fan. However, with all due respect, I feel the need to remind him that he is not the ‘richest black man’ – it is in fact my Godfather @AlikoDangote. Just clearing the air with #facts,” she wrote.